						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar to the left side of gate No. 5 of the Fort.</p>						

						<p>Rāmadēva, 1627 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Prabhava, Phālguṇa.</hi> As Rāmadēva was ruling between 1618-1630, we may equate the details viz., Prabhava, Phālguṇa to <hi rend="bold">1628 A.D., March.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of the village Turukapalle in Gutti to <hi rend="italic">jātikarta</hi> Nārāyaṇa by Bīravōli Tiruveṅgaḷanātharājulayyavāru.</p>						

						</summary>
